# App configuration.
# Copy this file to .env.local and set values to override the defaults.
#
# VITE_CONFIG_URL — URL of a remote REST endpoint that returns a JSON object
#   with runtime configuration for the app. Fetched once on load.
#   Values received from the API override all Vite build-time parameters below.
#   Expected JSON shape:
#     {
#       "stream_url":      "http://host:port/path",   // URL for MJPEG video stream
#       "settings_url":    "http://host:port/path",   // URL for settings page
#       "websocket_url":   "ws://host:port/path",     // WebSocket URL for gamepad/RSSI data
#       "gamepad_enabled": true                        // enable/disable gamepad support
#     }
#   Any key omitted from the response falls back to the Vite default below.
#   If not set, the app uses Vite build-time parameters exclusively.
#
# ── Vite build-time defaults (used when VITE_CONFIG_URL is absent or a key is missing) ──
#
# VITE_STREAM_URL — full URL of the MJPEG stream, including host, port and path.
#   Defaults to http://<page-hostname>:8080/stream if not set.
#   Example: http://192.168.1.10:8080/stream
#
# VITE_SETTINGS_URL — URL to redirect to when the Settings gear button is clicked.
#   If not set, the Settings button will not be rendered.
#
# VITE_GAMEPAD_ENABLED — set to "true" to enable HTML5 Gamepad API support.
#   When enabled:
#     - A gamepad connection indicator appears in the top-left corner.
#     - Gamepad polling starts/stops together with video playback.
#     - A prompt asks the user to press any button after playback starts.
#     - Gamepad state is forwarded as JSON over a WebSocket connection.
#   Defaults to "false" (feature disabled).
#
# VITE_WEBSOCKET_URL — WebSocket URL to send gamepad data to and receive
#   RSSI / signal information from controller.
#   Required when VITE_GAMEPAD_ENABLED=true.
#   Example: ws://192.168.1.10:9090/ws
#   The connection is opened when playback starts and closed when it stops.
#   Sent messages are JSON objects mirroring the browser's Gamepad API:
#     { id, index, connected, timestamp, mapping, axes, buttons }
#   Received messages are JSON objects that may contain RSSI/signal fields.
#
# Can also be passed inline when running the dev server:
#   VITE_CONFIG_URL=http://192.168.1.10/api/config npm run dev

VITE_CONFIG_URL=
VITE_STREAM_URL=
VITE_SETTINGS_URL=
VITE_GAMEPAD_ENABLED=false
VITE_WEBSOCKET_URL=
